                <h2><i class="fa-solid fa-terminal section-icon"></i> Bringing Code to Life</h2>
                <p>
                    Topic 7 taught you how to <em>design</em> algorithms; Topic 8 is about <em>building</em> them.
                    This chapter covers the practical skills needed to write, test, and refine working computer
                    programs.
                    You will learn to control data flow with loops and logic, organise code with functions and
                    procedures,
                    and handle data persistence using files.
                </p>
