            <!-- Section 8.1 Collapsible -->
            <details class="content-section" id="8.1">
                <summary>
                    <h3>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-code topic-icon"></i> 8.1 Programming Concepts</span>
                        <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down toggle-icon"></i>
                    </h3>
                </summary>

                <div class="section-body">
                    <h4>What you need to know:</h4>

                    <div class="learning-points">
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Basics:</strong>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Declare and use variables and constants.</li>
                                    <li>Understand and use basic data types (Integer, Real, Char, String, Boolean).</li>
                                    <li>Understand and use Input and Output statements.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Constructs:</strong>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><strong>Sequence:</strong> Instructions executed one after another.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Selection:</strong> IF statements and CASE statements (including
                                        nesting).</li>
                                    <li><strong>Iteration:</strong> Count-controlled loops (FOR), Pre-condition loops
                                        (WHILE), and Post-condition loops (REPEAT).</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Operations:</strong>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><strong>Totalling & Counting:</strong> Standard algorithms for summing and
                                        tallying.</li>
                                    <li><strong>String Handling:</strong> Length, Substring, Upper, Lower.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Operators:</strong> Arithmetic (+, -, *, /, ^, MOD, DIV), Relational (=,
                                        <, <=,>, >=, <>), and Logical (AND, OR, NOT).
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Subroutines:</strong>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Define and use Procedures and Functions (with or without parameters).</li>
                                    <li>Understand the difference between local and global variables.</li>
                                    <li>Use Library Routines (MOD, DIV, ROUND, RANDOM).</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Maintainability:</strong> Understand how to create a maintainable program
                                (meaningful identifiers, comments, indentation).
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Nested Notes Collapsible -->
                    <details class="notes-box">
                        <summary>
                            <h4>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-lightbulb"></i> Notes & Guidance</span>
