                        <div class="notes-content">
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>String Indexing:</strong> The first character of a string can be position 0
                                    or 1 depending on the language. In pseudocode, we often assume 1-based indexing
                                    unless specified.</li>
                                <li><strong>Nested Statements:</strong> You need to be comfortable nesting IFs inside
                                    Loops, Loops inside Loops, etc. (Max depth usually 3 levels).</li>
                                <li><strong>Procedures vs Functions:</strong> A <em>Procedure</em> performs a task but
                                    does not return a value. A <em>Function</em> performs a task and <strong>must return
                                        a value</strong>.</li>
                                <li><strong>Operators:</strong>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li><code>MOD</code> returns the remainder.</li>
                                        <li><code>DIV</code> returns the integer quotient (e.g., 7 DIV 2 = 3).</li>
                                        <li><code><></code> means "Not Equal To".</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </details>
