                    </h3>
                </summary>

                <div class="section-body">
                    <h4>What you need to know:</h4>

                    <div class="learning-points">
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Declaration:</strong> Declare and use one-dimensional (1D) and two-dimensional
                                (2D) arrays.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Usage:</strong> Understand the use of arrays to store multiple items of data
                                under a single identifier.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Iteration:</strong> Write values into, and read values from, an array using
                                iteration (loops).
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Nested Notes Collapsible -->
                    <details class="notes-box">
                        <summary>
                            <h4>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-lightbulb"></i> Notes & Guidance</span>
                                <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down toggle-icon"></i>
                            </h4>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="notes-content">
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Indexing:</strong> Use variables as indexes (e.g.,
                                    <code>MyArray[Index]</code>). The first index can be 0 or 1.
                                </li>
                                <li><strong>Nested Iteration:</strong> To traverse a 2D array (like a grid or table),
                                    you use a nested loop (an outer loop for rows, an inner loop for columns).</li>
                                <li><strong>Example:</strong> <code>StudentNames[1] = "Ali"</code> or
                                    <code>Grid[2,3] = 'X'</code>.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                </div>
            </details>

