                <summary>
                    <h3>
                        <span><i class="fa-solid fa-file-lines topic-icon"></i> 8.3 File Handling</span>
                        <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down toggle-icon"></i>
                    </h3>
                </summary>

                <div class="section-body">
                    <h4>What you need to know:</h4>

                    <div class="learning-points">
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Purpose:</strong> Understand the purpose of storing data in a file (permanent
                                storage that persists after the program closes).
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Operations:</strong> Open, close, and use a file for reading and writing.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Nested Notes Collapsible -->
                    <details class="notes-box">
                        <summary>
                            <h4>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-lightbulb"></i> Notes & Guidance</span>
                                <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down toggle-icon"></i>
                            </h4>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="notes-content">
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Modes:</strong> Files must be opened in a specific mode: <code>READ</code>
                                    or <code>WRITE</code>.</li>
                                <li><strong>Writing:</strong> <code>WRITEFILE</code> creates a new file or overwrites an
                                    existing one.</li>
                                <li><strong>Reading:</strong> <code>READFILE</code> reads data from an existing file
                                    (usually line by line).</li>
                                <li><strong>Closing:</strong> Always <code>CLOSEFILE</code> when finished to prevent
                                    data corruption.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                </div>
